    "createdAt": "2026-06-03T02:24:00.000Z",
    "diffSummary": "Persist conversation identity (title + avatar) so chat history shows the right name and avatar after a restart. Root cause: the realtime listener message model (zca-rust TMessage) carries only a sender display name and NO avatar, so store/db.rs save_message always wrote thread_avatar = None and a group thread's title became the last sender's name. Avatars/names only exist in the directory data the app already fetches (list_contacts via get_all_friends, list_groups via get_group_info), which was never persisted onto thread rows. Fix: types/stored.rs adds a ThreadIdentity DTO (thread_id + title + avatar, camelCase, no secrets); store/db.rs adds backfill_thread_identities(account_id, identities), which UPDATEs (never inserts) the title + avatar of threads that already exist using COALESCE so a missing/empty directory value never blanks a known one, and returns the updated-row count as a non-secret diagnostic; command/mod.rs list_contacts + list_groups now accept the store State and, after fetching the directory, map contacts/groups to ThreadIdentity and backfill existing thread rows (best-effort; a store error is logged, never fails the directory load). A directory entry with no conversation does not create a thread row. No realtime data source was added and the Tauri IPC argument shape is unchanged (the store State is injected, not passed from the webview), so no frontend change is needed — load_history already returns the persisted avatar/title.",
    "changedFiles": [
        "src-tauri/src/types/stored.rs",
        "src-tauri/src/types/mod.rs",
        "src-tauri/src/store/db.rs",
        "src-tauri/src/command/mod.rs"
    ],
